Overview

This project focuses on building a machine learningâ€“powered Early Warning System to predict the risk of climate-induced diseases (such as Dengue, Malaria, and Respiratory Illnesses) using climate data, air quality indicators, and epidemiological records.

The system leverages a data processing pipeline with robust preprocessing, class imbalance handling (SMOTE), and machine learning models to provide accurate predictions.

